Cleaner section parser, richer narrative, 1,090 reports total

Pulled the remaining ITP / FE / university Ofsted reports and tightened
the section parser so verbatim quotes don't trail into PDF page-footer
boilerplate. Three concrete improvements:

1. Reports coverage: 295 → 1,090 inspections with report_text.
   - fetch-itp-reports.ts ran with cap=800 after the cleaner parser was
     in place; an additional 795 reports parsed.
   - Findings extracted: 34,972 verbatim phrase matches across 2,815
     inspections (cleaner now — counts down from 55k because the parser
     stops cleanly at end-markers, no junk-text false positives).

2. Section parser is end-marker aware.
   - sections.ts now has an END_MARKERS list (Provider details / School
     details / Information about this inspection / Annex / page footers
     like "Inspection report: <name>") that terminate the current
     section without becoming a section themselves.
   - All occurrences are tracked via matchAll, so repeated page footers
     truncate every section that touches them.
   - Stricter min-length per key — F&S grade-table headers
     (Apprenticeships, Adult learning, Behaviour, Leadership, ...) need
     250+ chars of body to count as a real narrative section, otherwise
     they're suppressed (a 1-line grade snippet adds nothing the
     inspections columns don't already have).
   - Section keys for ITP / FE reports now use `what_provider_needs_to_improve`
     when the matched pattern was the provider-flavoured one.

3. Brief and detail page render the full narrative.
   - generate-itp-briefs.ts pulls 15 section keys per latest inspection,
     ordered actionable first: what to improve, areas for action,
     recommendations, then framework narrative (apprenticeships, adult
     learning, young people's provision, high needs, quality of
     education, behaviour, personal development, leadership,
     safeguarding) and finishes with the main-findings narrative.
   - /opportunities/[id] panel matches the brief's section list.
   - 328 briefs regenerated.

Sample improvement on a typical RI ITP brief: previously 50 lines of
"identity / pipeline signals / report URL". Now ~150 lines with the
inspector's verbatim "what does the provider need to do to improve"
bullets, the "areas for improvement" narrative, the safeguarding
finding, and the main "what is it like to be a learner" narrative —
all directly quotable in outreach.
